benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/allTags - Retrieve account tags

covered: Valid Request: Tests cover successful retrieval of all tags for an account with and without query parameters (e.g., TC01, TC02).
Empty Response: Account with no tags returns an empty JSON array (TC07).
Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of objectType, includedDeleted, and audit parameters including combinations and edge cases (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC20, TC21, TC22).
Authorization: Unauthorized access test returning 401 is included (TC10).
Error Handling: Coverage of common error codes including 404 (TC08), 400 (TC09, TC12, TC22), 503 (TC11), 504 (TC15).
Content-Type: Verification that response Content-Type is application/json (TC27).
Integration & State Variations: Tests for adding/deleting tags across APIs (TC18, TC19) and state variations like empty DB or soft-deleted accounts (TC25, TC26).
Regression/Edge Cases: Deleted tags included when includedDeleted is true (TC16) and min/max parameter scenarios (TC20, TC21).
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for server-side pagination or paging behavior with large tag sets.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling behavior.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or caching semantics.
Authorization: 403 Forbidden scenario not covered (only 401 tested).
ObjectType enumeration coverage: Only INVOICE and PAYMENT are explicitly tested; other supported object types and invalid enum values are not covered.
Performance verification: TC14 covers large datasets but lacks explicit paging/performance assertions across repeated runs or under load.
Soft-delete edge nuance: While TC26 covers soft-deleted accounts, additional edge cases around soft-deleted entities could be explored.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to validate paging behavior (page size, page number, total count) when account has many tags.
Extend authorization tests to cover 403 Forbidden scenarios and token expiration/privilege issues.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure the API handles bursts gracefully.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers and caching behavior.
Expand objectType coverage to include more of the supported object types and test invalid/edge enum values.
Enhance performance testing with explicit, repeatable load tests and paging validation on large tag sets (beyond TC14).
Include tests for additional 5xx internal errors to ensure proper handling of unexpected upstream failures (in addition to 503/504).
Consider adding explicit content negotiation/Accept header tests to validate responses under different client expectations.
